Aleki Lutui given two week suspension for foul play at Ospreys
Media playback is not supported on this deviceEdinburgh hooker Aleki Lutui has been given a two-week suspension for a reckless tackle on Tom Smith duringSaturday's 44-10 defeat at Ospreys.Lutui was cited after appearing to catch Smith near the face with a swinging arm as he was brought down at a ruck.Wednesday's hearing in Dublin concluded the challenge had been "reckless rather than intentional".Ospreys have since confirmed that Smith has a suspected dislocated knee.Tonga international Lutui, 35, moved to Edinburgh in the summer, having spent seven seasons at Worcester.